Here's a PlantUML component diagram capturing the static architecture of the Partydeck system, focusing on the general architectural concern:

```plantuml
@startuml itays123_partydeck

skinparam componentStyle uml2

cloud "Google Cloud Platform" {
  [Google Cloud Run] as GCR
  [Google Cloud Build] as GCB
}

package "Partydeck System" {
  [Panel] <<React Frontend>>
  [Game] <<React Frontend>>
  [Server] <<Java Backend>>
  
  database "Database" {
    [User Data]
    [Game Data]
  }
}

[Panel] -down-> [Server] : REST API
[Game] -down-> [Server] : WebSocket
[Server] -down-> [Database]
GCR -up-> [Panel]
GCR -up-> [Game]
GCR -up-> [Server]
GCB -up-> [Panel] : CI/CD
GCB -up-> [Game] : CI/CD
GCB -up-> [Server] : CI/CD

note right of [Panel]
  - User authentication
  - Deck management
  - Game initiation
end note

note right of [Game]
  - Real-time gameplay UI
  - Player actions
end note

note right of [Server]
  - Game logic
  - WebSocket communication
  - State management
end note

@enduml
```